Tracy Long 

		
		VP, Service, Building Solutions, North America, 

	
		 Johnson Controls International plc 	

 
Last Updated: 07/24/2017 



Executive Summary
Stanford MBA Tracy Long joined Tyco in 2009 as Director, Product Management and Marketing for Mechanical Products. In 2011, she was promoted to VP and General Manager, Fire Protection Products and in 2013, she was named President, Canada serving as the Country Manager for Tyco's 2,000-person installation and services business 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Long is married and has two children.
She graduated from Millburn High School in 1996. 
Current Focus

Company snapshot: Johnson Controls International Plc. is a multinational conglomerate headquartered in Cork, Ireland that produces automotive parts such as batteries and electronics and HVAC equipment for buildings. It  
Key Challenges

Realizing productivity and cost savings: In February 2017, executives at Johnson Controls International said cost savings from the merger with Tyco came in ahead of schedule during the first full quarter the two compani 
Biographical Highlights

Long holds a BA in social studies and economics from Harvard University (1996-2000).
She went on to earn an MBA from the Stanford Graduate School of Business in 2003. 
 





