Johnson Controls International plc Key Developments

Johnson Controls International plc Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Third Quarter and Nine Months Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 27 17
Johnson Controls International plc reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the third quarter and nine months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company has posted net sales of $7,683 million against $5,154 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations before income tax was $718 million against $480 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations was $629 million against $402 million a year ago. Net income attributable to JCI was $555 million against $383 million a year ago. Diluted earnings per share were $0.59 against $0.59 a year ago. Cash provided by operating activities was $215 million against $75 million a year ago. Capital expenditures was $362 million against $279 million a year ago.

For the nine months, the company has posted net sales of $22,036 million against $14,583 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations before income tax was $1,496 million against $1,163 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations was $926 million against $961 million a year ago. Net income attributable to JCI was $736 million against $303 million a year ago. Diluted earnings per share were $0.78 against $0.47 a year ago. Cash used in operating activities was $1,321 million against cash generated from operating activities of $696 million a year ago. Capital expenditures was $996 million against $822 million a year ago. Acquisition of businesses, net of cash acquired was $6 million against $133 million a year ago.


Johnson Controls Announces Executive Changes
Jul 26 17
Johnson Controls announced that it has named Michael Bartschat Vice President of the Johnson Controls Operating System (JCOS) in addition to his current role as Chief Procurement Officer, reporting to Chairman and CEO Alex Molinaroli. In this new role, Bartschat will lead the majority of the functions in the JCOS, including engineering, procurement, manufacturing, supply chain, and environment, health & safety. He will also have overall responsibility for the continuous improvement and real estate functions. Bartschat succeeds Jeff Williams, who has moved on to lead the company's Buildings business in Europe, Middle East and Latin America. Bartschat, who joined Johnson Controls in 2004, has held various leadership roles at the company. In addition to his role as chief procurement officer, he is also the integration leader for the merger between Johnson Controls and Tyco. In that role he has been responsible for realizing growth opportunities and delivering the value inherent in the combination of the two companies.


Johnson Controls International plc, Q3 2017 Earnings Call, Jul 27, 2017
Jul 10 17
Johnson Controls International plc, Q3 2017 Earnings Call, Jul 27, 2017


